    "body": "In the dict iteration code, some of the code paths used `CYTHON_AVOID_BORROWED_REFS` and some used `CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_PYPY`, resulting in broken state on GraalPy where one part of the exact-dict fast-path was active and one was not. It would end up calling `PyIter_Next` with a dict object instead of an iterator.\r\n\r\nThe existing test `iterdict` tests this AFAICS. Unfortunately, it's currently disabled on GraalPy. I had to fix one more thing on our side to make it pass. So I'm not adding any new test right now with the plan that after we release, we can enable the existing test.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-24T18:01:08Z",
